-- Obama Says `All Options' Must Be Examined to Keep Social Security Solvent
-- B y   T r a c i   M c M i l l a n   a n d   H a n s   N i c h o l s
-- 2010-10-14T20:37:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/obama-says-all-options-must-be-examined-to-keep-social-security-solvent.html
President Barack Obama said “all
options” are on the table to keep the Social Security system
solvent, including raising the cap on payroll taxes.  Obama, answering questions at a town hall carried live on
the Viacom Inc. cable channels BET, MTV, VH1 and CMT, said the
payroll tax for Social Security currently ends at $106,800.  “That could be modified or changed in a way that would
help
extend the solvency of Social Security,” Obama said, repeating
a stance he took during his presidential campaign  To contact the reporter on this story:
Traci McMillan in Washington at 
